<text>Potential Energy Curves and Activation Energy: Activation Energy
Try running the reaction again. You should notice that it is a lot easier for the atom and molecule to react this time. The way this is depicted in the graph is by showing a smaller potential energy increase during the collision. The amount of kinetic energy needed during a collision for a reaction is called the &quot;activation energy&quot;. The easier it is for a reaciton to happen, the lower the activation energy will be.

       
          
